    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-13T12:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-13T12:30:00-05:00" n="385"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.8830/2424: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-13T13:30:00-04:00"
                            >July 13, 1943—1:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–1175. Your despatches 10692<note n="81" xml:id="d385fn81">See footnote 80, <ref
                            target="#pg_412">p. 412</ref>.</note> and 10693 of June 23, 1943. Please
                    inform the Department whether the 39 additional small publications listed in
                    despatch 10692 import their own newsprint requirements direct or are supplied by
                    local distributors.</p>
                <p>The information concerning recommended quotas will be held strictly confidential
                    and Embassy’s suggestion will be followed. Mr. Agusti obtained his information
                    from his suppliers and was well versed with respect to the method of allotting
                    shipping space for newsprint before he called on officials of the
                    Department.</p>
                <p>Every effort will be made to suggest equitable newsprint distribution for all
                    consignees on Argentine vessels but, as has been previously stated to the
                    Embassy, loadings for Flota steamers are controlled in Buenos Aires.</p>
                <pb facs="0427" n="415" xml:id="pg_415"/>
                <p>In making monthly reports to the Department of newsprint received by each
                    consignee, please also include newsprint received from Sweden or other foreign
                    countries.</p>
                <p>The Department will attempt to keep the Embassy informed of all shipments of
                    newsprint to consignees in Argentina.</p>
                <p>Embassy’s report 10692 is extremely helpful and is appreciated by the
                    Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
